cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

This paper deals with visual localization, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a new method that incorporates deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions applications such as autonomous vehicles and assistive navigation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions experiments carried out on public datasets and in the field, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
